==Ancient Greek==

===References===
*[[Strong's concordance]] number:  [http://www.biblestudytools.net/Lexicons/Greek/grk.cgi?number=1080&version=kjv G1080] 

===Pronunciation===
*γεννάω / gennaō / ghen-nah'-o
=== Etymology ===

*From a variation of [[γένος]] {{GG|1085}}; 
=== Verb ===
to [[procreate]] (properly of the father, but by extension of the mother); figuratively to regenerate: - [[bear]], [[beget]], be born, bring forth, [[conceive]], be delivered of, [[gender]], [[make]], [[spring]].